{"ts":"2026-06-25T22:50:01.783Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Considering Component Library**\n\nI'm thinking about components. I've decided a React component library for inner pages is the way to go, separate from the landing page. It needs to be exquisite. Now, I am reviewing a list of components to determine which elements are critical to include in the library.\n\n\n**Defining Component Specifications**\n\nI've got a detailed list of inner page components to build and document: `InnerPageShell`, `InnerPageHero`, and on to `Carousel`. The design philosophy is clear: robust, dark-themed, pure Tailwind CSS, responsive, and accessible. SVGs and animations are key. I'm leaning toward organizing these under `/components/inner-pages` as separate files, though other arrangements remain in play.\n\n\n**Structuring Component Hierarchy**\n\nI've decided to create a `/components/inner-pages/` directory for organizational cleanliness and maintainability, exporting everything from an `index.ts` file. This is working well. I'm actively planning each component with meticulous detail, starting with `AnimatedBackgroundGrid` and `InnerPageShell`. The `AnimatedBackgroundGrid` will be a pure CSS/SVG marvel for the inner page background, and the `InnerPageShell` will integrate the `Header`, `Footer`, and standardized page spacing, plus the all important `AnimatedBackgroundGrid`.\n\n\n**Expanding Component Definitions**\n\nI'm now detailing several inner page components. I've been working on `InnerPageHero`, with a focus on a non-cluttered layout with breadcrumbs and title gradients. It will feature custom SVGs. I also defined `MotionReveal`, which supports multiple directions and considers `prefers-reduced-motion`. Finally, I'm working on `BentoGrid` which will be a premium grid of feature cards.\n\n\n**Defining New Inner Components**\n\nI'm now detailing some new inner components. I'm focusing on a `BentoGrid` that supports a mix of standard and custom spans for a rich card layout, with gridlines, glow effects, moving light borders, and dark backgrounds. Next, the `NarrativeSection` will have a split layout for editorial storytelling. It'll feature highlights, bullet points, and an option for the media side. Finally, the `ArchitectureDiagram` will be an interactive SVG showcasing enterprise AI architecture with animations and side-panel details.\n\n\n**Developing New UI Elements**\n\nI'm now detailing some new inner components. I'm focusing on an `OperatingModelTimeline` timeline with interactive highlights and pure CSS animations. Then, I'm designing an `EnterpriseFlowDiagram` for complex workflows with interactive nodes and paths. I'm also planning a `PlatformProductPreview` featuring a dark-themed mockup with interactive tabs and glowing elements. Finally, I'm considering an `IndustrySolutionMap` of interactive industry automation hotspots.\n\n\n**Expanding Component Scope**\n\nI'm now detailing some new inner components. I've been working on a `ResearchLibraryGrid` with filters for categories and a search bar, plus custom cards with tags and icons. Also, I'm conceptualizing a `GlobalHubMap` to leverage an existing world map component with interactive pins. Finally, I'm designing a `SecurePortalPreview` to abstractly present the Client Portal's secure features.\n\n\n**Adding More Components**\n\nI'm now detailing some new inner components. I've been focusing on a performant, touch-enabled `Carousel` with auto-scrolling, snap-scrolling, and drag support. I'm also planning the `RelatedPagesGrid` for the inner page footer. Finally, I'm working on a `PremiumCTA` block with a custom mouse glow, dual-action buttons, and trust badges, and small spec lists. All of these must be polished, robust, responsive, and avoid third-party dependencies!\n\n\n**Deciding Component Structure**\n\nI'm now certain: individual files under `/components/inner-pages/` is the way to go. This keeps imports clean and allows developers to grab exactly what they need. I'm finalizing the file structure, and created the following: `AnimatedBackgroundGrid.tsx`, `InnerPageShell.tsx`, `InnerPageHero.tsx`, `MotionReveal.tsx`, `BentoGrid.tsx`, `NarrativeSection.tsx`, `ArchitectureDiagram.tsx`, `OperatingModelTimeline.tsx`, `EnterpriseFlowDiagram.tsx`, `PlatformProductPreview.tsx`, `IndustrySolutionMap.tsx`, `ResearchLibraryGrid.tsx`, `GlobalHubMap.tsx`, `SecurePortalPreview.tsx`, and `Carousel.tsx`.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-25T22:50:01.786Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"ruojyeg7","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/components/inner-pages/AnimatedBackgroundGrid.tsx","new_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport React, { useEffect, useState } from \"react\";\n\nexport default function AnimatedBackgroundGrid() {\n  const [shouldAnimate, setShouldAnimate] = useState(true);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const mediaQuery = window.matchMedia(\"(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)\");\n    setShouldAnimate(!mediaQuery.matches);\n\n    const handleChange = (e: MediaQueryListEvent) => {\n      setShouldAnimate(!e.matches);\n    };\n\n    mediaQuery.addEventListener(\"change\", handleChange);\n    return () => mediaQuery.removeEventListener(\"change\", handleChange);\n  }, []);\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"absolute inset-0 -z-50 w-full h-full bg-[#010101] overflow-hidden pointer-events-none\">\n      {/* Premium Ambient Glow Pools (Brand Colors: Red and Blue) */}\n      <div \n        className={`absolute top-[-10%] left-[-10%] w-[60%] h-[60%] rounded-full bg-[#E4000F]/8 blur-[140px] md:blur-[220px] mix-blend-screen ${\n          shouldAnimate ? \"animate-[pulse_10s_infinite_alternate]\" : \"\"\n        }`} \n      />\n      <div \n        className={`absolute bottom-[-10%] right-[-10%] w-[60%] h-[60%] rounded-full bg-[#009DFF]/8 blur-[140px] md:blur-[220px] mix-blend-screen ${\n          shouldAnimate ? \"animate-[pulse_12s_infinite_alternate_reverse]\" : \"\"\n        }`} \n      />\n      <div \n        className=\"absolute top-[40%] left-[30%] w-[40%] h-[40%] rounded-full bg-[#E4000F]/3 blur-[120px] md:blur-[180px] mix-blend-screen\" \n      />\n\n      {/* SVG Fine Grid Overlay */}\n      <div className=\"absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.07] bg-[linear-gradient(to_right,#ffffff_1px,transparent_1px),linear-gradient(to_bottom,#ffffff_1px,transparent_1px)] bg-[size:4rem_4rem] [mask-image:radial-gradient(ellipse_60%_50%_at_50%_50%,#000_70%,transparent_100%)]\" />\n\n      {/* Subtly Glowing Grid Crosses */}\n      <div className=\"absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.12] bg-[radial-gradient(#ffffff_1px,transparent_1px)] bg-[size:4rem_4rem] [mask-image:radial-gradient(ellipse_60%_50%_at_50%_50%,#000_70%,transparent_100%)]\" />\n\n      {/* Futuristic Laser Scanner Lines */}\n      {shouldAnimate && (\n        <div className=\"absolute inset-0 w-full h-full opacity-[0.02]\">\n          <div className=\"absolute left-0 right-0 h-[2px] bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-[#E4000F] to-transparent animate-[scan_8s_linear_infinite]\" />\n          <div className=\"absolute top-0 bottom-0 w-[2px] bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent via-[#009DFF] to-transparent animate-[scanVertical_12s_linear_infinite]\" />\n        </div>\n      )}\n\n      {/* Noise/Grain Overlay for High-End Premium Texture */}\n      <div \n        className=\"absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.015] pointer-events-none\"\n        style={{\n          backgroundImage: `url(\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg viewBox='0 0 200 200' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cfilter id='noiseFilter'%3E%3CfeTurbulence type='fractalNoise' baseFrequency='0.8' numOctaves='3' stitchTiles='stitch'/%3E%3C/filter%3E%3Crect width='100%25' height='100%25' filter='url(%23noiseFilter)'/%3E%3C/svg%3E\")`,\n        }}\n      />\n\n      {/* Style definitions for custom animations */}\n      <style jsx global>{`\n        @keyframes scan {\n          0% { top: -10%; }\n          100% { top: 110%; }\n        }\n        @keyframes scanVertical {\n          0% { left: -10%; }\n          100% { left: 110%; }\n        }\n      `}</style>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n"}}}
