{"ts":"2026-06-25T22:54:46.856Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"tj8dz5rj","input":{"summary":"I have successfully created the requested global design system for all public inner pages. All files were created inside the `/components/inner-pages/` directory, leaving the approved landing page, landing sections, and homepage files completely untouched (verified by git status).\n\nHere is a summary of the 17 premium, responsive, and accessible components created under `components/inner-pages/`:\n\n1.  **AnimatedBackgroundGrid**: Pure CSS/SVG background with slow-pulsing ambient red/blue glow pools, glowing gridlines, laser scanning animation, and noise texture. Gracefully halts motion for accessibility.\n2.  **InnerPageShell**: A wrapper for public inner pages that integrates Header, Footer, and the AnimatedBackgroundGrid, setting up responsive padding-top of 84px to prevent fixed Header overlap.\n3.  **InnerPageHero**: An intro component featuring breadcrumbs, category pills, custom high-contrast headings with glowing accents, and an interactive inline abstract network-mesh SVG component that responds to mouse hover.\n4.  **MotionReveal**: Smooth viewport scroll animation utilizing motion/react. Uses custom easing (easeOutExpo) and queries system prefers-reduced-motion to seamlessly disable animation behavior for reduced motion needs.\n5.  **BentoGrid / BentoCard**: Premium hover-tracking feature cards that support custom metrics, badges, and render a subtle brand-colored (red-to-blue) hover spotlight gradient following mouse coordinate positions.\n6.  **NarrativeSection**: Editorial story layout with left/right media alignment options. Bullet list with custom SVG checkmarks and a simulated telemetry console window showing scrolling live server checks.\n7.  **ArchitectureDiagram**: Fully interactive SVG architectural flowchart representing enterprise AI stack ingestion, cognitive orchestration, memories, and actions. Users click different layers to reveal details, and dashes animate computational flow.\n8.  **OperatingModelTimeline**: Vertical-to-horizontal responsive timeline showing GFF AI's active phases (Garage, Foundry, Factory). Includes active stage selection highlighting, duration indicators, and deliverables.\n9.  **EnterpriseFlowDiagram**: Interactive SVG workflow showcasing loops, routing, agent evaluation, human audit blocks, and API dispatcher. Hovering nodes shows spec files.\n10. **PlatformProductPreview**: Functional mock administrative dashboard with Sidebar tabs for overview (with a live SVG chart graph), logs (with search filters), and guardrails (with interactive toggle switches).\n11. **IndustrySolutionMap**: Grid map tracking autonomous solutions in Finance, Manufacturing, and Logistics. Tapping industry badges displays detailed action-agent subcomponents.\n12. **ResearchLibraryGrid**: Document list with category filter tags and a fully-functioning client-side query search bar. Download action buttons simulate live file packaging using loading spinners and alert popups.\n13. **GlobalHubMap**: Local map highlighting global computing centres (New York, Zurich, Tokyo, Singapore) with interactive pins, pulse circles, and hover-triggered regional SLAs.\n14. **SecurePortalPreview**: Sandbox gating component displaying SOC2 metrics, encryption standards, and a custom padlock SVG that rotates open/closed with client state clicks.\n15. **Carousel**: Snap-scrolling card showcase with responsive next/prev navigation buttons, auto-scroll bounds, hover pause triggers, and full accessibility overrides.\n16. **RelatedPagesGrid**: Footer directory suggesting next steps. Hovering cards smoothly translates chevron vectors with premium CSS ease.\n17. **PremiumCTA**: Large dual-action banner with beautiful brand gradients, custom cursor spotlight glow, and trust badges (SOC2 sandbox, GDPR guardrails, AES-256 lock).\n\nAll of these are exported cleanly from `components/inner-pages/index.ts`. The project was built successfully via `npm run build` with zero TypeScript errors or failures. No backend modules, AWS, or slug routes were added.","verified":true}}}
